DESCRIPTION:Join member Dionne Ford and her co editor Jill Strauss\, as the
 y discuss their anthology <i>Slavery's Descendants: Shared Legacies of Race
  and Reconciliation. </i>The work<i>&nbsp\;</i>is included in the Montclair
  Public Library's observance of the 400th anniversary of the first enslaved
  African's arrival at Jamestown in 1619. This event is co-sponsored by our 
 own Undoing Racism Committee.<br><br><br>More information about the event i
 s here: <br>http://www.montclairlibrary.org/news-events/slaverysdescendants
 /
