CREATED:20200810T185552Z
DESCRIPTION:\nA Rosh Hashanah service at UUCM\n6pm\, Saturday September 19t
 h \n(Hebrew: רֹאשׁ הַשָּׁנָה\, literally "head of the year") is the Jewish 
 New Year. This High Holiday celebration with Rev. Anya Sammler-Michael will
  be co-led by our congregation's new Jewish Unitarian Universalist  Underst
 anding group. All are welcome and all ages may appreciate our multifaceted 
 worship. \nIf possible\, prepare sliced apples and honey\, to participate i
 n the closing blessing which will remind us of the sweetness possible\, in 
 the year to come. 
LAST-MODIFIED:20200810T185618Z
LOCATION:via Zoom
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:A Rosh Hashanah service at UUCM
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
