DESCRIPTION:We will celebrate the Northern spring equinox\, which falls on 
 March 20\, which divides the light and dark halves of the year. Ostara is a
  commonly used name for the holiday\, and the root word of Easter\, from wh
 ich Easter got its name. This ritual will be in the Druidic path.<br><br>Al
 l are welcome to Sacred Wheel CUUPs events. For more information\, <a href=
 "mailto:sacredwheelcuups@uumontclair.org">contact Ann Trip</a> or visit us 
 on <a href="http://facebook.com/groups/UUCMSacredWheel">Facebook</a>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20220127T171949Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Ostara Ritual
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20170916T193000Z
DTEND:20170916T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T022957Z
UID:0vi3n3d90m62gd483k0e71hu6m@google.com
CREATED:20170906T140458Z
DESCRIPTION: Along with the Anti-Racist Alliance of North Jersey and The Af
 ricana Institute of Essex County College\, I am pleased to attach our flyer
  with RSVP link for the Sat Sept 16 Gubernatorial Town Hall on Racial Justi
 ce event\, doors open at 330 pm\, 4-6 program.  \n\nWe are awaiting answers
  from Guadagno and Murphy campaigns and will update registrants on news on 
 their answers.  \n\nWe ask that you rsvp to event itself.  If you/ UUCM mem
 bers and friends might volunteer their time to help out\, we need help  in 
 signing-in\; directions\, info tables\, question collecting\, public relati
 ons. We'll need persons in two hour blocks  from 2-7 pm.  Parking info will
  eventually appear on the eventbrite invite\, as soon as that is finalized.
   email me if you can help.\n\nDr. Akil Khalfani of Essex Co College and Dr
 . Janice Johnson Dias\, President of the GrassROOTS Foundation\, will co-mo
 derate.  It will be a great event to educate persons about issues of racial
  disparities in NJ regarding criminal justice\, cild welfare\, education\, 
 immigrant rights\, health/mental health\, environment\, housing\, employmen
 t\, segregation and more.\n\nWe are pleased to have many cosponsors who wil
 l share this information with their constituencies and provide questions to
  our confirmed candidates.
LAST-MODIFIED:20170906T140458Z
LOCATION:Essex County College\, Smith Hall\, West Market & MLK Blvd.\, Newa
 rk\, NJ 
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:GUBERNATORIAL TOWN HALL ON RACIAL JUSTICE
TRANSP:OPAQUE
ATTACH;FILENAME=TownHall-Governors-event2017_wlink.pdf:https://drive.google
 .com/a/uumontclair.org/file/d/0B0ajsUXj78RRYUdudjQ0TzJrM0U/view?usp=drive_w
 eb
END:VEVENT
