UID:161vjblgqeuoapkp9cre4psrkv@google.com
CREATED:20210310T003745Z
DESCRIPTION:Beginning in October on Zoom\, UUA/ Our Whole Lives Parents and
  Caregivers as Sexuality Educators - Small Group Ministry Sessions In a sma
 ll group setting\, adults explore their roles as the most important sexuali
 ty educators their children will have. The information and attitudes that a
 dults share with their children—intentionally or by default—carry extraordi
 nary power. It is a power that many adults struggle to wield effectively an
 d confidently. Often\, their own experiences\, perspectives\, and worries g
 et in the way. These sessions invite parents and caregivers to find support
  and courage with one another. The 60-minute sessions use a small group min
 istry format to engage adults in topics including Gender Identity\, Relatio
 nships\, Social Media\, and Consent. This group is for parents and caregive
 rs of any age children or youth. Once a month via zoom starting Monday\, Oc
 tober 19\, and Monday\, November 16\, 7 to 8pm.&nbsp\;<br><br><a href="mail
 to:owl@uumontclair.org" id="ow8471" __is_owner="true">For more information<
 /a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210621T225109Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Parents and Caregivers as Sexuality Educators - Small Group Ministr
 y Sessions
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
