CREATED:20190606T133940Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a day long workshop on how to better welcome people
  of various identities to our UU communities. Through experiential learning
 \, this workshop aims to help leaders\, greeters and membership professiona
 ls better anticipate the needs and wishes of guests by staying open to hear
 ing them. We’ll learn how to move away from our assumptions and become bett
 er accustomed to putting those preconceived notions on hold in favor of aut
 hentic listening and acceptance.<br><br>This workshop will be led by Patric
 ia Infante and Rev. Dr. Hope Johnson\, Congregational Life Staff in the Cen
 tral East Region.<br><br>Cost is $25 per person and includes lunch. *Please
  register by August 16\, 2019 to ensure availability of lunch.* We cannot g
 uarantee lunch for walk-ins!<br><br><a href="https://uua.wufoo.com/forms/z1
 dvefhp0b3rus9/" id="ow1628" __is_owner="true">Register Now!</a>&nbsp\;
LAST-MODIFIED:20190606T133940Z
LOCATION:UU Congregation of Princeton 50 Cherry Hill Rd Princeton\, NJ 0854
 0-7626
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Multicultural Welcome Workshop
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
