UID:02p8v617uup9ebnlm2beerqt48@google.com
CREATED:20210303T145824Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Do you or someone you love have lived experience with mental
  health problems? Today about 20% of the adult population are diagnosed wit
 h a mental health problem. Yet\, even now it is often viewed through the le
 ns of intolerance\, ignorance\, and fear.</p><p>We are pleased to host UU R
 ev. Barbara Meyers for the workshop<br>“Showing Up for Each Other’s Mental 
 Health”</p><p>This online Zoom presentation and discussion will be held on 
 Saturday\,<br>April 17\, from 1:00 – 3:00 pm&nbsp\;<em>with a 10 minute bre
 ak in the middle.</em></p><p>Rev. Meyers is a UU community minister with a 
 mental health ministry based in Fremont\, California\, and President of the
  Board of the&nbsp\;<a href="https://uumentalhealth.org/">UU Mental Health 
 Network</a>&nbsp\;. She is the author of a mental health curriculum\, video
 s\, TV shows\, publications for congregations\, and the book&nbsp\;<a href=
 "https://www.uuabookstore.org/Held-P18680.aspx">HELD – Showing Up for each 
 Other’s Mental Health</a>&nbsp\;\, published by Skinner House Books in Augu
 st 2020\, (available through the UUA bookstore and Amazon)</p><p>In this wo
 rkshop\, Rev. Barbara Meyers will discuss</p><ul><li>Stories from her menta
 l health ministry - both how-to stories and how-not-to stories - giving gui
 dance for congregants in the pews who want to help make a difference.</li><
 li>Show the importance of spiritual resources and peer groups</li><li>Discu
 ss the impact that COVID is having on mental health and what people can do 
 to mitigate it</li><li>The Unitarian Universalist Mental Health Network and
  it’s recent survey of mental health in the denomination</li></ul><p>A $20 
 per person donation is welcomed but not required.&nbsp\;</p><p>REGISTER HER
 E</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210304T145759Z
LOCATION:via Zoom
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Showing up for each others mental health
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
