DESCRIPTION:<p style="">Are you interested in retaining autonomy at the end
  of your life? Did you know that In 2019 New Jersey authorized the time-tes
 ted practice of Medical Aid in Dying (MAiD)? MAiD allows a terminally ill a
 nd mentally capable adult to request from their doctor a prescription for m
 edication that the patient can then decide to self-ingest in order to die p
 eacefully.&nbsp\; Want to learn more?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p style=""><br></p>
 <p style="">Join us on February 7 when Mary Moriarty of The Funeral Consume
 rs Alliance of Northern NJ will delve into this topic in greater detail.&nb
 sp\; Attendance is free\; please register at <a href="mailto:fcannj@gmail.c
 om" style="">fcannj@gmail.com</a> to receive the Zoom link.&nbsp\;</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220125T162750Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Presentation on Medical Aid in Dying
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
