DESCRIPTION:Sacred Wheel CUUPs is holding a Winter Solstice ritual on Sunda
 y\, December 19 at 7:30 PM via Zoom. The Winter Solstice is the shortest da
 y of the year. It takes place on the 21st or 22nd of December (Northern Hem
 isphere). We know today that the Sun will return\, because of the course of
  the Sun and through scientific exploration of other planets in our solar s
 ystem. Our ancestors did not take the return of the Sun for granted\, and i
 n addition\, they were suffering much more under the hardships of severe wi
 nter weather than we do today. Join us as we welcome the return of the Sun.
  For more info on Sacred Wheel\, email&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:sacredwheel@uu
 montclair.org">sacredwheel@uumontclair.org</a>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20211118T172023Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Winter Solstice ritual
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
