CREATED:20210712T211533Z
DESCRIPTION:We will gather with all ages and all species on the front lawn 
 of our Congregation<br><br><a href="https://onrealm.org/uumontclair/PublicR
 egistrations/Event?linkString=ODdlMjI0OTQtNGFkNC00ZDRhLThhZWYtYWQ2MzAxNWUyM
 jg5" id="ow11068" __is_owner="true">REGISTER HERE</a><br><br><br>With joy\,
  song and ritual we will bless our pets\, and our dear stuffed animals.&nbs
 p\;<br><br>This service draws from the inspiration of St. Francis of Assisi
 . In this Unitarian Universalist version we will take a moment to grieve th
 e animals that have died\, share our gratitude for the animals that make ou
 r lives better\, bless the animals that make their home among us\, and comm
 it to treating our animals like partners not things.<br><br>Please bring do
 nations of pet food\, treats\, used towels\, or monetary&nbsp\;contribution
 s to serve animals in local shelters.&nbsp\;
LAST-MODIFIED:20210712T211533Z
LOCATION:67 Church St\, Montclair\, NJ 07042\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Animal Blessing
TRANSP:OPAQUE
