CREATED:20210519T201334Z
DESCRIPTION:UUCM Sacred Wheel CUUPs is hosting a virtual Litha (Summer Sols
 tice)&nbsp\;ritual on Friday\, June 18 at 7:30 PM via Zoom. The summer sols
 tice\, also known as midsummer\, occurs when one of the Earth's poles has i
 ts maximum tilt toward the Sun. It happens twice yearly\, once in each hemi
 sphere. The sun reaches its highest position in the sky and is the day with
  the longest period of daylight. It is also known as Litha or in Druidry as
  Alban Hefin meaning 'The Light of the Shore.' If you have an altar set up 
 send us photos to share.<br><br><a href="https://zoom.us/j/97622408006?pwd=
 VW1heXl3Ylc1bmRTeCtOVUJiMjgwQT09" id="ow985" __is_owner="true">CLICK HERE T
 O JOIN</a><br>Pw: UUCM<br>.<br>All are welcome to Sacred Wheel CUUPs events
 . Email&nbsp\;Ann Trip at:<a href="mailto:sacredwheelcuups@uumontclair.org"
 >sacredwheelcuups@<u></u>uumontclair.org</a>&nbsp\;for more info or visit u
 s on Facebook:&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/UUCMSacredWhe
 el/?__cft__[0]=AZX9K-hg7LCCjfkkqTofZ7UgUWdnU9emhN5hvaLbWuz-9Q5GyhCWJtM8dfAx
 O1Vgv3dLpaewD1b-N_LCVtBSSZ7TLfRxNJZbwUrZEtyegSkPlGaxaTupYzVxMeTW_lQ3MxoW4FD
 S23CKbRRJUPYSX029&__tn__=q">facebook.com/groups/<u></u>UUCMSacredWheel</a>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20210519T201406Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Virtual Litha hosted by Sacred Wheel CUUPs 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
