DESCRIPTION:<strong>UU’s for Jewish Awareness</strong>&nbsp\;is open to all
  members and friends of UUCM who have Jewish roots or relatives and/or an i
 nterest in learning more about Jewish customs and culture. Led by UUCM memb
 ers Hilary Fandel\, Marcia Mandel and Helen Lippman\, the group will provid
 e an opportunity to honor Jewish heritage\, share cultural and religious me
 mories\, and explore feelings about dual identity as UU and Jewish. Much of
  the focus will be shaped by the interests and needs of attendees.
LAST-MODIFIED:20210310T003837Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Rabbi Charles Arian to Speak to Jewish Awareness Group
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20211120T223000Z
DTEND:20211120T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T022957Z
UID:7qvsti6av2g7tdgdnmtik1np04@google.com
CREATED:20211014T154028Z
DESCRIPTION:All are welcome to join in this observance of remembrance\, mou
 rning\, and affirmation. Hosted by the Montclair Interfaith Clergy Associat
 ion\, this service will be held outside at&nbsp\;<a href="https://r20.rs6.n
 et/tn.jsp?f=001McwbpGmExoFfhSyRHA1W6aq0Pp1vksVgvc7ybfIebDAcQ6fhu_kY17NWztUQ
 t9FQfXyFUckqVNpBK6pEHywVxS16QgWSf--puqKcgcNE3sk1chH7X95EKqYea5YoyRjYJDRgxJW
 Y5raUv6yfBbck7Qj_qEVzN3-Hiumu1Mj-WmQxNjLheHQcZA==&amp\;c=9bnezZfgnK1QgZSKA5
 7kECdaRjiaAkj4T5N1Dfn-ghSzAzWRi-JGLg==&amp\;ch=nweFvEBLBABlfaiNg7QHXC9O6rLH
 RPYgzIRATiIhqRTGi1KDBCisZQ==">B’nai Keshet Reconstructionist Synagogue&nbsp
 \;</a>on Saturday\, November 20\, 2021\, at 5:30 PM.&nbsp\;<br><br>The Tran
 sgender Day of Remembrance is set aside to memorialize those who were kille
 d due to anti-transgender hatred or prejudice. With this service we raise p
 ublic awareness\, mourn and honor the lives of our transgender and gender n
 on-conforming kin and we express love and respect in the face of national i
 ndifference and hatred.&nbsp\;<br><br>The Transgender Day of Remembrance wa
 s started in 1999 by transgender advocate Gwendolyn Ann Smith as a vigil to
  honor the memory of Rita Hester\, a transgenderwoman who was killed in 199
 8. The vigil commemorated all the transgender people lost to violence since
  Rita Hester’s death\, and began an important tradition that has become the
  annual Transgender Day of Remembrance.<br><br><a href="mailto:revanya@uumo
 ntclair.org" id="ow6622" __is_owner="true">Questions can be directed to Rev
 . Anya Sammler-Michael.</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20211026T180858Z
LOCATION:Bnai Keshet\, 99 S Fullerton Ave\, Montclair\, NJ 07042\, USA
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Transgender Day of Remembrance
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
