DESCRIPTION:The Women's International League for Peace & Freedom will host 
 a speaker from the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) at their Wednesday
 \, May 1 meeting.\n\nAccording to a news release from the group\, the publi
 c meeting will take place at 7 p.m. in the Annex Building of the Montclair 
 Cooperative School at 65 Chestnut Street in Montclair.\n\nParticipants can 
 learn about some of the issues the ACLU is currently in litigation over. A 
 Q&A session and light refreshments will follow the presentation.
