BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20211014T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20211014T203000
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;WKST=SU;UNTIL=20211120T045959Z;BYDAY=TH
DTSTAMP:20260311T022957Z
UID:4hjg3b0ldg5ujp95o5eojerso1@google.com
CREATED:20210712T212406Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><b><a href="https://onrealm.org/uumontclair/PublicRegistrati
 ons/Event?linkString=NjI5MzJjY2QtYTc5Mi00YTg0LWJjZjUtYWQ4NjAwZjJlN2Yx" id="
 ow1301" __is_owner="true">REGISTER HERE</a></b></p><p><b>Great Works Series
  2021</b></p><p>A Theology for the Social Gospel: A Bold New Vision for Fai
 thful Social Justice - based on the book by Walter Rauchenbusch</p><p>Liber
 al Baptist Walter Rauschenbusch is credited with popularizing the notion th
 at the Abrahamic Traditions - Islam\, Judaism and Christianity - are more p
 roperly seen as calling for a just social order\, where we see sin more as 
 a matter of social systems\, bad pubic policy\, and the need to assure that
  the fruits of human labor and industry are shared with the widest possible
  number of people. He cites the Bible as proof\, and his case is not only c
 onvincing it is authoritative.</p><p>Rev Scott will guide us through this t
 ext and share the relevant Bible passages supporting this vision of social 
 salvation.&nbsp\;</p><p>You will need to purchase the text (only $1.48 on K
 indle!) and get a good Study Bible to use as well. 6 Thursdays from Oct 14 
 thru Nov 18\, 7-830pm\, in Peierls and Virtual.</p><p>Only $10 to register!
  Class capped at 50.</p><p><br></p><p><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/pr
 oduct/1891396528/ref=ewc_pr_img_2?smid=ATVPDKIKX0DER&amp\;psc=1" id="ow1314
 " __is_owner="true">Purchase the text here</a></p><p>More on this text: “Th
 e Social Gospel movement was a Protestant Christian intellectual movement t
 hat was most prominent in the late 19th century and early 20th century. The
  movement applied Christian ethics to social problems\, especially social j
 ustice\, inequality\, alcoholism\, crime\, racial tensions\, slums\, bad hy
 giene\, child labor\, weak labor unions\, poor schools\, and the danger of 
 war. Theologically\, the Social Gospel claims it is a moral imperative for 
 humankind to rid itself of social evils by human effort. Most were theologi
 cally liberal\, although they were typically more conservative when it came
  to their views on social issues. Walter Rauschenbusch was one of the leade
 rs of this important Christian movement.”</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20211028T230927Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference\, UUCM-1-Peierls (60)
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Adult RE: Great Works Series: A Theology for the Social Gospel\; Wa
 lter Rauschenbusch and His Bold New Vision for Faithful Social Justice
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
