CREATED:20210316T140004Z
DESCRIPTION:UUCM Sacred Wheel CUUPs is hosting a Beltaine (May Day) celebra
 tion. Beltaine also known as May Day is a Gaelic festival. It is most commo
 nly held on May 1\, which is the halfway point between Ostara\, the spring 
 equinox and Litha\, the summer solstice. Historically\, it was widely obser
 ved throughout Ireland\, Scotland and the Isle of Man. Participants are ask
 ed to have something for "cakes and ale" to be able to join in at that time
  of the rite.<br><a href="https://zoom.us/j/98137123604?pwd=WW1WYmRVVkQybGx
 jMjludW92RkRYUT09" id="ow7185" __is_owner="true">Join Zoom Meeting</a>&nbsp
 \;<br>Meeting ID: 981 3712 3604&nbsp\;<br>Passcode: UUCM
LAST-MODIFIED:20210316T213111Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Sacred Wheel CUUPs Beltaine
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
