UID:3pt1ictjlisv5vnejpdf30vhb9@google.com
CREATED:20211118T172534Z
DESCRIPTION:Imbolc or Imbolg\, also called Brigid’s Day\, is a Gaelic tradi
 tional festival marking the beginning of spring. Most commonly it is held o
 n 1 and 2 February\, or about halfway between the winter solstice and the s
 pring equinox. Historically\, it was widely observed throughout Ireland\, S
 cotland and the Isle of Man. <a href="mailto:sacredwheel@uumontclair.org" i
 d="ow691" __is_owner="true">Contact for more information.&nbsp\;</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20211118T172534Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference
