BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20181017T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20181017T210000
DTSTAMP:20260311T022957Z
UID:47r1i9t85ddjmq46kvf18nts2l@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20181017T190000
CREATED:20180517T143306Z
DESCRIPTION:\nWeeks 1 & 2 - (Sep 26 and Oct 3) - we will focus on Book I - 
 the overal history of the region and the war itself and The Spartan Debate\
 , 432 BCE (1.66-88)\; plus the beginning of Book Two (2.1-17)\;  \n\nWeek 3
  – (Oct 10) - We will discuss Pericles' Funeral Oration (Book 2.34-46)\;The
  Policy of Pericles\, 430 B.C. (Book 2.56-65)\;\n\nWeek 4 – (Oct 17) - The 
 Siege of Plataea\, 429 B.C. (2.71-78)\, The End of Plataea\, 427 B.C. (3.51
 -68)\; The Plague\, 430 B.C. (2.47-55)\; Civil War in Corcyra\, 427 B.C. (3
 .69-85).\n\nWeek 5 – (Oct 24) We will engage both The Mytilenean Debate\, 4
 27 BCE (3.35-3.50)\; and The Melian Dialogue\, 416 BCE (5.84-5.116)\; \n\nW
 eek 6 – (Nov 7) Book VI\, because it most vivdly portrays a democracy in de
 cline.\nThere are many versions of this great book.\nThe Strassler is here:
 \nhttp://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0684827905/ref=ox_sc_act_title_1?ie=UTF8
 &m=ATVPDKIKX0DER\n\nThere are any free online versions\, including here: ht
 tp://www.greektexts.com/library/Thucydides/History_of_The_Peloponnesian_War
 _-_Book_I/eng/243.html\n\nand here: http://classics.mit.edu/Thucydides/pelo
 pwar.html\n\nVideos- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5KeZ8KdTacU
LAST-MODIFIED:20181012T142749Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Adult RE- Great Books\; Thucydides
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20210318T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20210318T203000
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;WKST=SU;COUNT=3;BYDAY=TH
DTSTAMP:20260311T022957Z
UID:1ep7ghj9sb4q5771tnbk7cousd_R20210318T230000@google.com
CREATED:20201214T154316Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Part of UUCM’s “8th Principle Project”</p><p><br></p><p>Join
  UUCM member Dionne Ford-Kurtti\,&nbsp\;Intern Minister Ali Bell-Delgado an
 d Rev. Scott on a deep-dive into the classic text of Womanist theology\,&nb
 sp\;Sisters in the Wilderness: The Challenge of Womanist God-Talk\, by Delo
 res S. Williams. Womanist Theology is theology from the perspective of Blac
 k Women\, though one needn’t be black or female in order to be deeply rewar
 ded for engaging this seminal text.</p><p><br></p><p>We will help set this 
 text into context\, teach theological thinking\, highlight how our life’s s
 tories are the building blocks of any good theology\, and learn how to ‘rea
 d against the grain’ the histories of white supremacy\, patriarchy and othe
 r oppressions. We also aim to empower and equip attendees to compose their 
 own stories in the spirit of Narrative and Identity Theology.</p><p><br></p
 ><p>The class runs for 5 consecutive Thursdays - from Feb 25 thru March 25\
 , 7-830pm. Registration is $10.&nbsp\;</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210316T214130Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Sisters in the Wilderness: The Challenge of Womanist God-Talk
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
