UID:3l3572jmjkr3md4tqttnsfb5ep_R20210321T150000@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20210425T110000
CREATED:20200507T193119Z
DESCRIPTION:You are invited to join us for our virtual Connection Café ever
 y Sunday at 11:00 AM via Zoom.&nbsp\;<br><br><b><i>On Sunday\, April 25\, t
 he Council on Ministries will be hosting a Town Hall focused on the UUCM Re
 ligious Education program. Town Hall will take place during Connection Cafe
  at 11 am and will be led by John Wodnick with support from other CoM membe
 rs. Topics will include feedback on RE for children\, senior youth\, and ad
 ults\, as well as other topics highlighted during the Listening Circle. The
 re will be an opportunity for interactive discussion about ways to improve 
 the RE program and to acknowledge what's working well right now. We look fo
 rward to seeing you there.&nbsp\;</i></b><br><b><i><br></i></b><br><a href=
 "https://zoom.us/j/98495539203">CLICK HERE TO JOIN NOW</a><br>Phone # +1 92
 9 205 6099/ ID: 984 9553 9203<b><i><br></i></b><br>If you haven’t yet exper
 ienced our online Connection Café\, give it a try. Participants report that
  this format allows us to build relationships across the congregation in wa
 ys that will sustain us as individual participants and support our growth a
 s a community. So grab your coffee and join us for a fun way to connect on 
 Sunday morning. All are welcome. We hope you can join us!&nbsp\;<br><br><a 
 href="https://zoom.us/j/98495539203">CLICK HERE TO JOIN NOW</a><br>Phone # 
 +1 929 205 6099/ ID: 984 9553 9203
LAST-MODIFIED:20210930T140402Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Connection Cafe/Town Hall on Religious Education
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
