BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20210327T200000Z
DTEND:20210327T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T022957Z
UID:2ji56b7ph8k4b5tf081rdfiorv@google.com
CREATED:20210303T224509Z
DESCRIPTION:<blockquote><p>March's&nbsp\; theme at UUCM is commitment\, and
  it's also Women's History month. Thinking of great roles for women\, Mutte
 r Courage leapt to mind\, but Brecht's indomitable sufferer tries to profit
  from war and lacks a commitment to justice. From there via Lynn Nottage's 
 Ruined\, Sweat followed.&nbsp\; Nottage won the 2017 Pulitzer Prize for thi
 s difficult\, unflinching look at working class residents of Reading\, Penn
 sylvania\, set in a bar and toggling between a present and the past.&nbsp\;
 It is a powerful vehicle for exploring commitment to friendship\, equity\, 
 and those overlooked in today's economy.&nbsp\;</p><p>Sweat contains adult 
 language and themes (never fear\, a multigenerational show is coming\, as i
 s comedy\, and Shakespeare) so is suitable for participants over 16. As we 
 covenant to exploring theater together\, we will arrive at consensus about 
 how to approach Nottage's use of the N-word in her script. If any of you ha
 s strong feelings about its utterance versus the euphemism "N-word" please 
 comment.&nbsp\; It would be helpful to have RSVPs via Realm indicating if y
 ou are willing to read\, planning to listen only\, or not interested in thi
 s one. I will send the script via Realm about a week before.</p><p><br></p>
 </blockquote>
LAST-MODIFIED:20210316T193157Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Theater Group
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
