BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20220128T000000Z
DTEND:20220128T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T022957Z
UID:2su0lfm5631tn2cgbva7fm4cfs@google.com
CREATED:20220106T230305Z
DESCRIPTION:<p style=""><a href="https://onrealm.org/uumontclair/PublicRegi
 strations/Event?linkString=NDFjY2QyMWYtZDMxOC00OGNmLTgzZjYtYWUxNTAxN2I4ZjYx
 " id="ow708" __is_owner="true" style="">REGISTER HERE</a></p><p style="">Th
 e Leadership Support Council (LSC) is a new UUCM group formed by the Nomina
 ting and Leadership Development Committee (NLDC)&nbsp\;The LSC consists of 
 long-time congregational members who support present and future UUCM leader
 s through bi-monthly round tables\, discussion\, and advising to cultivate 
 growth and address leadership questions.</p><p style="">Kickoff Meeting&nbs
 p\;</p><p style="">On Thurs\, Jan 27\, 2022\, 7-8 pm\, the first LSC Round 
 Table will feature Nancy and Tim Franklin\, former UUCM members and princip
 als of <a>Franklin Solutions</a>\, who will deliver an interactive presenta
 tion entitled “Moral Dimensions of Leadership.” Topics such as trust\, incl
 usion\, diversity\, and integrity will be discussed during this&nbsp\; 30-m
 inute discussion.</p><p style="">This is a discussion that is open to All U
 UCM members. Current and future team/group leaders are encouraged to join t
 he presentation during the first half of the Jan 27th meeting and participa
 te in the conversation to follow. Nancy and Tim\, as well as LSC members\, 
 will be happy to address any follow-up questions and leadership-related tho
 ughts brought up by attendees.&nbsp\;</p><p style="">Please join us for thi
 s timely Zoom talk by <a href="https://onrealm.org/uumontclair/PublicRegist
 rations/Event?linkString=NDFjY2QyMWYtZDMxOC00OGNmLTgzZjYtYWUxNTAxN2I4ZjYx" 
 id="ow738" __is_owner="true" style="">registering on REALM </a>&nbsp\;and e
 mail <a style="">nldc@uumontclair.org</a>&nbsp\; with any questions. We loo
 k forward to seeing you on Jan. 27th!</p><b><br></b><p style=""><i style=""
 >What is the Nominating and Leadership Development Committee (NLDC)?</i></p
 ><p style=""><i>The NLDC is a committee defined in the UUCM by-laws\, consi
 sting of 6 members of the congregation. The NLDC engages members of the con
 gregation in life-long leadership development\, skills training\, and educa
 tion. It develops new leaders\, empowers existing leaders\, and nominates&n
 bsp\; potential Board and NLDC members\, so that each can cooperatively and
  faithfully serve the Mission and Vision of our congregation. Current NLDC 
 members are: Laura Anthony\, Dana Moore\, Jill Wodnick\, Matt Silverman\, R
 oz Gohagan\, and Doug Andrews</i></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220106T230305Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Leadership Support Council (LSC) Kickoff Event
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
