BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20221019T230000Z
DTEND:20221020T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T022957Z
UID:2re3e7o6dgl4hhbpfllccp4mck@google.com
CREATED:20220801T194711Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><a href="https://onrealm.org/uumontclair/PublicRegis
 trations/Event?linkString=NzQ4MjAyY2MtNmM3MC00OWQzLThhOWUtYWVlNDAxNDViMjhm"
 >REGISTER HERE</a><br><br><p>The Archives Team (Irene Sanderson\, Becky Dog
 gett\, Jerry Fried\, Jane Gaertner\, Chris Glickson) has been working hard 
 to preserve our history and make it accessible to members and others intere
 sted in our significant achievements and culture. This year is our 125th an
 niversary\, and we’re looking back to see where we’ve&nbsp\;<strong><b>BEEN
 </b></strong>&nbsp\;and understand where we&nbsp\;<strong><b>ARE</b></stron
 g>.<br></p><p><br></p><p>We’ve enlisted the help of professional archivists
  and historians to help delve into our own history and put it into the cont
 ext of social justice and theological movements over the years. UUs from ou
 r congregation have always “shown up” to stand for a better\, more inclusiv
 e democracy and have been a big part of social movements as well as a signi
 ficant ethical and theological voice for justice and equality. From our “fo
 unding mothers” to our current and expanding crop of fledgeling ministers\,
  UUCM members have been at the heart of the UU movement\, a big part of its
  successes and failures.</p><p><br></p><p>After our first public meeting ov
 er Zoom in Oct 2021 at which we heard from our three prior ministers and en
 listed the memories of several of our longtime members\, we wanted to follo
 w up with a little exploration of “what we have accomplished” over the year
 s. Towards that end\, we’ll be showcasing a few fascinating artifacts from 
 our history and putting these documents in their appropriate historical con
 text.</p><p><br></p><p>Please join us on Weds October 19th\, either on Zoom
  or in the Peierls&nbsp\;Room. Hope to see you then!</p></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220809T134610Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference\, UUCM-1-Peierls (60) [Multiplatform]
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Archives Public Event
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
