CREATED:20221114T164440Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><br>The Winter Solstice is the shortest day of the y
 ear. It takes place on the 21st or 22nd of December (Northern Hemisphere). 
 We know today that the Sun will return\, because of the course of the Sun a
 nd through scientific exploration of other planets in our solar system. Our
  ancestors did not take the return of the Sun for granted\, and in addition
 \, they were suffering much more under the hardships of severe winter weath
 er than we do today. Join us as we welcome the return of the Sun..&nbsp\;Al
 l are welcome.<br>&nbsp\;For more info on Sacred Wheel\, email&nbsp\;<a hre
 f="mailto:sacredwheel@uumontclair.org">sacredwheel@uumontclair.org</a>.</ht
 ml-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20221114T164502Z
LOCATION:UUCM-1-Alliance (10) [Multiplatform]
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Sacred Wheel CUUPs Winter Solstice Ritual
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
