UID:5pvajbdj3hemops8jhdqake4gm@google.com
CREATED:20220517T183339Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u>Sacred Wheel CUUPs is hosting a multi-platfor
 m&nbsp\;<b>Litha</b>&nbsp\;(Summer Solstice)&nbsp\;ritual. The summer solst
 ice\, also known as midsummer\, occurs when one of the Earth's poles has it
 s maximum tilt toward the Sun. It happens twice yearly\, once in each hemis
 phere. The sun reaches its highest position in the sky and is the day with 
 the longest period of daylight. It is also known as Litha or in Druidry as 
 Alban Hefin meaning 'The Light of the Shore.'&nbsp\;<br><u></u></html-blob>
 <br><html-blob><br></html-blob><br><html-blob>All are welcome to Sacred Whe
 el CUUPs events. For more information\, <a href="mailto:sacredwheelcuups@uu
