CREATED:20220803T131726Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><a href="https://onrealm.org/uumontclair/PublicRegis
 trations/Event?linkString=NDE0ZDFmMDYtZjNjNC00MzVkLTllZDctYWVlYzAxMTJlNjQ2"
  id="ow4507" __is_owner="true">REGISTER HERE</a></html-blob><br><html-blob>
 <br></html-blob><br><html-blob>What do you say when a relative\, friend or 
 acquaintance&nbsp\;asks you about your congregation? How do you explain wha
 t it means to you to be a Unitarian Universalist?&nbsp\;This engaging&nbsp\
 ;workshop style class will guide participants through a series of exercises
 --personal reflection\, role-play\, and discussion--that will equip them to
  communicate their liberal religious ideals. The authors of this curriculum
  are co-ministers that&nbsp\;are dear friends and colleagues of Rev. Scott 
 and Rev. Anya\, Barbara and Jaco Ten Hove. Come hungry to develop new muscl
 es with which to convey your values. Leave with a deeper understanding of y
 ourself and the vision to which your life is dedicated.<br><u></u><u></u></
 html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220809T164156Z
LOCATION:UUCM-1-Peierls (60) [Multiplatform]
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY: Unitarian Universalist Theology: "Articulate your UU Faith"  
TRANSP:OPAQUE
