CREATED:20170908T135441Z
DESCRIPTION:Host: Undoing Racism Committee\nPresenter:  James Williams IV \
 , Juvenile Justice Field Organizer\, New Jersey Institute for Social Justic
 e\n150 YEARS IS ENOUGH!!!\nIT’S TIME TO CLOSE THE JAMESBURG AND HAYES  YOUT
 H PRISONS\n              YOUTH JUSTICE NJ COALITION/NJ INSTITUTE FOR SOCIAL
  JUSTICE\n            Thursday\, October 19th\nRALLY FOR OUR YOUTH  at 5p.m
 .\nCHURCH STREET PLAZA( Bloomfield Ave/Fullerton Street)\, Montclair\nORGAN
 IZE FOR OUR YOUTH \n\nLight refreshments will be served 6-645 p.m.\nUNITARI
 AN UNIVERSALIST CONGREGATION AT MONTCLAIR\n        67 CHURCH STREET\, MONTC
 LAIR\n\nProgram begins at 6:45 p.m.   Ends 8 p.m.\nGuest Speaker:   James W
 illiams\,\nNew Jersey Institute for Social Justice\nHear about community ba
 sed alternatives to incarceration for youth. It’s time to disrupt  the crad
 le-to-prison pipeline.\nSponsored by the Undoing Racism Committee of UUCM. 
 Contact Jane Gaertner: uucmurc@gmail.com\n\n\nSetup at 6PM\n60 chair setup 
 in two rows with a middle aisle\nProjector and screen set up in front of st
 age\nCoffee hours table to stay where they are\nSmall round table by door\n
 Two tables by library with two chairs at each\nPodium on stage\nTwo chairs 
 and one table on stage
LAST-MODIFIED:20221206T042846Z
LOCATION:Fletcher Hall
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Juvenile Injustice:  150 Years Is Enough
TRANSP:OPAQUE
