DESCRIPTION:Sacred Wheel CUUPs will be holding a multi-platform&nbsp\;<b>Lu
 ghnasadh&nbsp\;</b>ritu<wbr>al..&nbsp\;Also known as&nbsp\;Lammas\, or Firs
 t Harvest\, it marks the beginning of the harvest season. The festival's na
 me is&nbsp\;Gaelic for “Commemoration of Lugh\,” Lugh is an Celtic God and 
 a member of the Tuatha Dé Danann. Although the sabbat is named after Lugh\,
  it is associated with his foster mother&nbsp\;Tailtiu\, who cleared the wa
 y for the introduction of agriculture in Ireland. An announcement with date
  and time to come.&nbsp\;<br><br>All are welcome to Sacred Wheel CUUPs even
 ts. For more information\, <a href="mailto:sacredwheelcuups@uumontclair.org
 "><u>contact Ann Trip</u></a> or visit us on <a href="http://facebook.com/g
 roups/UUCMSacredWheel"><u>Facebook</u></a>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20220616T183444Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference\, UUCM-1-Alliance (10) [Multiplatform]
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:UUCM Sacred Wheel- Lughnasadh Ritual
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
