DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20220929T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20220929T203000
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;WKST=SU;UNTIL=20221112T045959Z;BYDAY=TH
DTSTAMP:20260311T022957Z
UID:56k5bprmo0u18195l01s6coruu@google.com
CREATED:20220725T151240Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><a href="https://onrealm.org/uumontclair/Publ
 icRegistrations/Event?linkString=NmNlZTRkYzUtYWZiOS00NzdiLTlmYTktYWVlODAxNT
 dlYzBh">REGISTER HERE</a><br><br><p><b>125 Years of Relentless&nbsp\;Love:<
 /b>&nbsp\;<b>We Were There\, Making a Difference</b></p><p><br></p><p>This 
 year's Great&nbsp\;Works Program is jointly led by Rev Scott and the UUCM A
 rchives Team. In honor of UUCM's 125th&nbsp\;Anniversary\, we will examine 
 how this congregation has tackled the major issues of the day. After an ini
 tial session reviewing UUCM's overall history\, we will examine a different
  issue each week. Using sermons delivered from our pulpit\, actions taken b
 y our congregation\, and words shared in our sacred space by leading&nbsp\;
 lights of various justice movements - from W.E.B. DuBois to Gloria Steinem 
 to Pauli Murray. We will conclude by composing statements to UUCM'ers of th
 e future!&nbsp\;</p><p>Beginning September 29th\, join us for 7 consecutive
  Thursdays\, 7-830pm\, in the Peierls Room. Like all our major programming\
 , this course will be multiplatform\,&nbsp\;so you can Zoom in\,&nbsp\;alth
 ough we encourage&nbsp\;you to attend in person.</p><p>$20 registration&nbs
 p\;Fee (scholarships available).</p><p><br></p><p>7 Sessions:</p><p>1) Arch
 ives/History and Presentation (Virtual Tour)</p><p>2) Women’s Rights</p><p>
 3) Rise of Fascism</p><p>4) Peace/War/Disarmament</p><p>5) Racial Justice</
 p><p>6) Economic/Worker’s Justice&nbsp\;</p><p>7) What do you want the Gran
 dchildren to say about us? We will compose&nbsp\;statements about what the 
 UUCM Great Works class in 2072 might hopefully say about us! We will also d
 ecide how to share the class with the congregation.</p><u></u></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220809T165445Z
LOCATION:UUCM-1-Peierls (60) [Multiplatform]
SEQUENCE:3
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Adult RE Great Works 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20220410T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20220410T120000
DTSTAMP:20260311T022957Z
UID:n4uqholin9d12pqjc48nl5c097@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20220410T110000
CREATED:20200507T193119Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob>What happens if we all bring a little something to c
 ontribute to a communal pot of soup? Let’s find out. Bring some carrots\, o
 nions\, squash\, celery\, any kind of vegetable you like in soup. Bring a g
 rain like barley or a legume like lentils. Bring chopped kale or whole cabb
 age. Bring a can of mushrooms. Bring what you can. Bring it to the worship 
 service. It will be collected during our Time for all Ages and then turned 
 into something amazing (and vegan) by our Youth Group and our MESH (Montcla
 ir Emergency Services for Hope) cooking crew! After the service we will enj
 oy this communal creation<br><br><br><u></u><u></u></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220609T153115Z
LOCATION:UUCM-1-Fletcher Hall (306)
SEQUENCE:8
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Themed Connection Cafe- Stone Soup 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
