BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20200326T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20200326T210000
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;WKST=SU;COUNT=3;BYDAY=TH
DTSTAMP:20260311T022957Z
UID:4rdckj0bivuf58mnq97cnmt24u_R20200326T233000@google.com
CREATED:20190627T161025Z
DESCRIPTION:You need to be on zoom.<br>Go to zoom\, download and install\, 
 and familiarize yourself with the program. -&nbsp\;<br>Class meets via Zoom
  Meeting.&nbsp\;<br>Zoom meeting ID will be sent out via REALM and email.<b
 r><br><br>Get yourself a good study bible\, and any other reputable materia
 l to help you understand it.<br><br>Here are the notes for the class going 
 Forward:<br><p>"For the remainder\, we will focus on Mt 21 thru the end of 
 the text (28)\, including diving back into the Jewish scriptures referred t
 o in Matthew\; Prepare Mt 21-24&nbsp\;in this way for next time.<br></p><p>
 Some key poof texts: Isaiah - 7-9\; Is 53\;&nbsp\;Micah 5.2\; Psalms 7\; 11
 8\; Maccabees...</p><p>Matthew ‘Hebrew Prophet Fulfillment language” - foun
 d in Matthew&nbsp\;1:22\; 2:5-6\, 15\, 17-18 &amp\;&nbsp\;23\; 3:3\; 4:14-1
 6\; 8:17\; 12:17-21\; 13:35\; 21:4-5\; 26:31\, 54\, 56\; 27:9-10.<br></p><p
 >Jesus’s Hebrew name is&nbsp\;<strong>Yeshua</strong>&nbsp\;- a form of Jos
 hua - meaning: deliverer\, forgiver.&nbsp\;<br></p><p><strong>The Pharisees
 </strong>&nbsp\;were a social movement and a school of thought in the Holy 
 Land during the time of Second Temple Judaism. After the destruction of the
  Second Temple in 70 CE\, Pharisaic beliefs became the foundational\, litur
 gical and ritualistic basis for Rabbinic Judaism. Their insistence on the b
 inding force of oral tradition (“the unwritten Torah”) still remains a basi
 c tenet of Jewish theological thought. Leaders called rabbis. Working class
 . Worship could happen away from the Jerusalem Temple</p><p><strong>Sadduce
 es</strong>&nbsp\;- a member of a Jewish sect or party of the time of Jesus
  Christ that denied the resurrection of the dead\, the existence of spirits
 \, and the obligation of oral tradition\, emphasizing acceptance of the wri
 tten Law alone. Leaders called priests or Sanhedrin. Upper class\, aristocr
 atic. Temple worship only.</p><p><br>Sincerely\,<br>Rev Scott Sammler-Micha
 el</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20221206T043938Z
LOCATION:Zoom Meeting
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Engaged Theology: Spring Bible Study
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
