DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><p>Beltaine also known as May Day is a Gaelic festiv
 al. It is most commonly held on May 1\, which is the halfway point between 
 Ostara\, the spring equinox and Litha\, the summer solstice. Historically\,
  it was widely observed throughout Ireland\, Scotland and the Isle of Man.&
 nbsp\;</p><p>All are welcome to Sacred Wheel CUUPs events. For more informa
 tion\, <a href="mailto:sacredwheelcuups@uumontclair.org">contact Ann Trip</
 a> or visit us on <a href="http://facebook.com/groups/UUCMSacredWheel">Face
 book</a>.</p></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220425T193154Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference\, UUCM-1-Alliance (10)
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:UUCM Sacred Wheel- Beltaine Ritual
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
