UID:1v7h2k5vsqc3gh41qvmn937bkd@google.com
CREATED:20171003T125415Z
DESCRIPTION:Our 11th annual Pre-Holiday Fair Trade Show and Sale will be he
 ld on Sunday\, December 3rd\, from 10:00 AM-1pm in the Alliance Room.  This
  year\, we will feature goods from Rain Lily as well as Women Helping Women
 .  Enjoy the wonderful assortment of fair trade jewelry\, scarves and more 
 from Asian\, Indian \, Guatemalan and Ecuadorian fair trade artisans\, plus
  the exciting new woven and alpaca goods from Ecuador - children’s clothing
  and shawls and more. Your purchases help to improve the lives of women eng
 aged in these handicrafts and the lives of their families. Katie Mahoney\, 
 owner of Rain Lily\, and Gayle Jones\, a fellow UU from Plainfield and one 
 of the founders of Women Helping Women\, will donate a generous percentage 
 of their sales to our UUCM. \nRain Lily and Women Helping Women will be sup
 porting our Auction again this year\, as well\, with their donated goods fo
 r a beautiful Fair Trade Basket! Visit www.rainlilyshop.com to preview some
  of the items for the upcoming show and sale or contact Francesca Elms at f
 rancescaelms@verizon.net for more information.\n\nSetup: The sofas and furn
 iture were pushed back to the walls as much as possible\, with two large ta
 bles in an L shape.
