UID:6vr3efdj7ljj0fv38m0sseucne@google.com
CREATED:20170828T132052Z
DESCRIPTION:Andrea Lerner\, the UUA Central East Region Director of Congreg
 ational Life\, will be facilitating a StartUp for Revs. Anya and Scott\, Ch
 ris Buja\, the Board of Trustees\, various Committee Chairs and other lay l
 eaders on Saturday\, October 28th\, from 9:00 AM to 3:00 PM. The startup pr
 ocess is designed to assist the ministers and staff who are new to a congre
 gation\, their colleagues\, lay leaders and congregants to get to know one 
 another better at the start of their relationship. This is done through an 
 exploration of the congregation’s history\, its current functioning and “cu
 lture”\, and mutual hopes for the future. Through this process of sharing a
 nd familiarization\, a set of goals and action steps can be identified to g
 uide all parties through the initial period of adjustment. The clarificatio
 n of expectations\, goals\, and ways of relating at the beginning helps to 
 establish a stable and healthy environment in which all can grow and flouri
 sh. There will be sessions in the morning and afternoon.
LAST-MODIFIED:20221206T044624Z
LOCATION:Alliance\, Fletcher Hall\, Mortenson\, Sanctuary
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:New Staff Start-Up Workshop
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
