DESCRIPTION:For more information on the Nominating and Leadership Developme
 nt Committee please email <a href="mailto:NLDC@uumontclair.org">NLDC@uumont
 clair.org</a><br><br>UUCM A is inviting you to a scheduled Zoom meeting.<br
 ><br>Join Zoom Meeting<br><a href="https://us06web.zoom.us/j/86946586237?pw
 d=SzZlN0UxeVVNbndWSmVyS3Fvc21PQT09"><u>https://us06web.zoom.us/j/8694658623
 7?pwd=SzZlN0UxeVVNbndWSmVyS3Fvc21PQT09</u></a><br><br>Meeting ID: 869 4658 
 6237<br>Passcode: UUCM<br>One tap mobile<br>+16465588656\,\,86946586237#\,\
 ,\,\,*876560# US (New York)<br>+16469313860\,\,86946586237#\,\,\,\,*876560#
  US<br><br><br><br><p><b>Leadership Summit </b></p><p><b></b><br></p><p><b>
 Pre-Meeting - </b><b>Friday April 21st\, 12pm</b></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>
 <p><b>Leadership Summit Purpose: </b></p><ul><li>Work together to achieve o
 ur mission\, vision\, and strategic plan.</li><li>Set a visional focus for 
 the coming congregational year.</li><li>Break down silos through collaborat
 ion across program and ministry areas.</li><li>Plan ahead to increase oppor
 tunities\, outreach and in-reach.</li><li>Serve leaders with core informati
 on and the means for support.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><b>Agenda: 
 </b></p><p><br></p><p><b>Chalice lighting and Grounding Words</b></p><p><b>
 </b><br></p><p><b>Reflection on the Purpose</b> </p><p><br></p><p><b>Review
  -</b> “Care. Courage. Community.”</p><p><br></p><ul><li>What successes did
  we have toward Care? </li><li>What successes did we have toward Courage? <
 /li><li>What successes did we have toward Community? </li></ul><p><br></p><
 p><br></p><p><b>Setting a Visional Goal for 2023-24</b></p><p><b></b><br></
 p><ul><li>What are our greatest opportunities? </li><li>What are our greate
 st challenges? </li></ul><p><b></b><br></p><p><b></b><br></p><p><b>Preparin
 g for the Leadership Summit</b></p><ul><li>22 Leaders are signed up to atte
 nd\, others have received a direct invite</li><li>Review Agenda    </li></u
 l><p><b></b><br></p><p><b>Closing: </b>Likes and Wishes</p><p><br></p><p><b
 ></b><br></p><p><b></b><br></p><p><b></b><br></p><p><b></b><br></p><p><b>Le
 adership Summit</b></p><p><b>Thursday May 18th: 7-9:30pm </b></p><p><b></b>
 <br></p><p>Suggestion for Multi-platform Inclusion: That in-person attendee
 s bring a device so that they can also connect virtually. </p><p><b></b><br
 ></p><p><b>7pm - Welcome</b></p><ul><li>Chalice Lighting - Sarah Scalet</li
 ><li>Grounding Reading - Nicole Gray</li></ul><p><b></b><br></p><p><b>7:10p
 m - Review the purpose of the meeting</b></p><p><b></b><br></p><p><b>7:15pm
  - Breakout Groups</b></p><ul><li>Name\, Pronouns</li><li>Current Leadershi
 p Roles</li><li>What are the greatest opportunities for our congregation\, 
 now? </li><li>What are the greatest challenges for our congregation\, now? 
 </li><li>How do these opportunities and challenges intersect with your lead
 ership?</li></ul><p><br></p><p><b>7:30</b> Report back to full room</p><p><
 b></b><br></p><p><b></b><br></p><p><b>7:40 Considering our Visional Goal</b
 ></p><ul><li>Celebrate the Successes of “Care. Courage. Community.” </li><l
 i>Announce the goal for 2023-24<ul><li>Reflections</li><li>Ideas</li><li>In
 spirations</li></ul></li></ul><p><br></p><p><b></b><br></p><p><b>Break </b>
 </p><p><b>                </b></p><p><b>8:00 - Report from the Board of Tru
 stees*</b></p><p>The incorporation of the 8th Principle into the charge for
  your team/council/ministry. </p><ul><li><b></b>Why is a charge important?<
 /li><li><b></b>What is the 8th Principle work important? </li><li><b></b>Ex
 ample of the Out Front Charge </li></ul><p><br></p><p><b>8:15 - Report form
  the Council on Ministries*</b></p><p>The Strategic Plan and how leaders ca
 n engage with the Strategic Plan</p><ul><li>Where to find the Strategic Pla
 n</li><li>The Council on Ministries role</li><li>How to make changes/update
 s to the Strategic Plan</li></ul><p><b></b><br></p><p><b>8:30 - Report from
  the Nominating and Leadership Development Council* </b></p><p>Harvest the 
 Power </p><ul><li>How Harvest has been changed</li><li>How to engage as a l
 eader</li><li>How to nominate participants</li></ul><p><b></b><br></p><p><b
 ></b><br></p><p><i>*Note on Reports: Include meeting days and times\, where
  to find information. </i></p><p><br></p><p><b>Resources: </b></p><ul><li><
