DESCRIPTION:On Thursday November 30th our congregation hosted an evening of
  deep listening\, where our Muslim and Jewish interfaith colleagues spoke t
 heir lament regarding the terrorist attack on October 6th and the unfolding
  war in Gaza. After each spoke\, a 'first witness' offered a short prayerfu
 l affirmation and invited the community to say "I hear you. I love you." <b
 r><br>We at UUCM could use a similar space\, a space to hear\, be heard\, a
 nd process in community the totality of our concern. <br><br>Our sharing wi
 ll be guided by a covenant. We will practice deep listening and will respon
 d to one another's sharing with reverence and a sincere interest to underst
 and. <br><br><span>We will hold a series of these conversations\, for as lo
 ng as they are needed. </span><br><br>Questions can be directed to <a href=
 "mailto:revanya@uumontclair.org">revanya@uumontclair.org</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231214T160952Z
LOCATION:UUCM-1-Alliance (10) [Multiplatform]
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:A Space to be Heard and Held by Community 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
