UID:3fi2il4bmtajl7q9jnlu9nq6fd@google.com
CREATED:20230602T141501Z
DESCRIPTION:<u></u><u></u>Sacred Wheel CUUPs is hosting a multi-platform <b
 >Litha</b> (Summer Solstice) ritual. The summer solstice\, also known as mi
 dsummer\, occurs when one of the Earth&#39\;s poles has its maximum tilt to
 ward the Sun. It happens twice yearly\, once in each hemisphere. The sun re
 aches its highest position in the sky and is the day with the longest perio
 d of daylight. It is also known as Litha or in Druidry as Alban Hefin meani
 ng &#39\;The Light of the Shore.&#39\; <br><u></u><u></u><br><u></u><br><u>
 </u><br><u></u>All are welcome to Sacred Wheel CUUPs events. For more infor
 mation\, <a href="mailto:sacredwheelcuups@uumontclair.org" target="_blank">
 <u>contact Ann Trip</u></a> or visit us on <a href="https://www.google.com/
 url?q=http://facebook.com/groups/UUCMSacredWheel&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=cale
 ndar&amp\;ust=1686147266699915&amp\;usg=AOvVaw3OmHA8HrMTtI5sYJY-6wWt" targe
 t="_blank"><u>Facebook</u></a>.<br><u></u>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230602T141623Z
LOCATION:UUCM-1-Alliance (10) [Multiplatform]
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:UUCM Sacred Wheel CUUPs Litha Celebration
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
