CREATED:20210726T214116Z
DESCRIPTION:The UU’s for Jewish Awareness Group has invited Rabbi Dan Ehren
 krantz to speak on the subject of his book\, WHERE ARE YOU? A BEGINNER’S GU
 IDE TO ADVANCED SPIRITUALITY\, at 7:30 on May 15<sup>th</sup> via Zoom. We 
 invite everyone who is interested to join us!<strong><br></strong><br><stro
 ng><br></strong><br><strong>UU’s for Jewish Awareness</strong> is open to a
 ll members and friends of UUCM who have Jewish roots or relatives and/or an
  interest in learning more about Jewish customs and culture. Led by UUCM me
 mbers Hilary Fandel\, Marcia Mandel and Helen Lippman\, the group will prov
 ide an opportunity to honor Jewish heritage\, share cultural and religious 
 memories\, and explore feelings about dual identity as UU and Jewish. Much 
 of the focus will be shaped by the interests and needs of attendees. <a hre
 f="mailto:jewishawareness@uumontclair.org">For more information contact Mar
 cia. </a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230906T144503Z
LOCATION:Zoom Video Conference
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:UU for Jewish Awareness [invites Rabbi Dan Ehrenkrantz]
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
