UID:44u6qvtc34tenu57c1krpm6pp2@google.com
CREATED:20231214T161046Z
DESCRIPTION:On Thursday November 30th our congregation hosted an evening of
  deep listening\, where our Muslim and Jewish interfaith colleagues spoke t
 heir lament regarding the terrorist attack on October 6th and the unfolding
  war in Gaza. After each spoke\, a &#39\;first witness&#39\; offered a shor
 t prayerful affirmation and invited the community to say &quot\;I hear you.
  I love you.&quot\; <br><br>We at UUCM could use a similar space\, a space 
 to hear\, be heard\, and process in community the totality of our concern. 
 <br><br>Our sharing will be guided by a covenant. We will practice deep lis
 tening and will respond to one another&#39\;s sharing with reverence and a 
 sincere interest to understand. <br><br><span>We will hold a series of thes
 e conversations\, for as long as they are needed. </span><br><br>Questions 
 can be directed to <a href="mailto:revanya@uumontclair.org" target="_blank"
 >revanya@uumontclair.org</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231214T161048Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:A Space to be Heard and Held by Community 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
