DESCRIPTION:Sacred Wheel CUUPs will be holding a multi-platform Lughnasadh 
 ritual. Also known as Lammas\, or First Harvest\, it marks the beginning of
  the harvest season. The festival’s name is Gaelic for “Commemoration of Lu
 gh\,” Lugh is an Celtic God and a member of the Tuatha Dé Danann. Although 
 the sabbat is named after Lugh\, it is associated with his foster mother Ta
 iltiu\, who cleared the way for the introduction of agriculture in Ireland.
  We will meet multi-platform in the Alliance Room and via Zoom: <a href="ht
 tps://www.google.com/url?q=https://us06web.zoom.us/j/83187501343&amp\;sa=D&
 amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1716041023317461&amp\;usg=AOvVaw3Frgiqb04ZPk1
 tZMN957eW" target="_blank">https://us06web.zoom.us/j/83187501343</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240513T140406Z
LOCATION:UUCM-1-Alliance (10) [Multiplatform]
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Sacred Wheel CUUPs Lughnasadh Ritual 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
