DESCRIPTION:All are welcome to join our annual interfaith Yom HaShoah\, Hol
 ocaust commemoration\, hosted by the Montclair Interfaith Clergy Associatio
 n\n\nAs part of our service\, we will have the privilege of delving into th
 e stories of Torah scrolls rescued from the Holocaust\, each housed within 
 our local synagogues. Rabbi Norman Patz will guide us through the narrative
 s of these scrolls and their communities\, serving as powerful testimonies 
 to a tradition that endured despite unimaginable adversity. Together\, we w
 ill honor the memory of those who perished and celebrate the resilience of 
 our heritage as we listen to the sacred words read aloud.
LAST-MODIFIED:20240429T144845Z
LOCATION:Temple Ner Tamid\, 936 Broad St\, Bloomfield\, NJ 07003\, USA
SEQUENCE:3
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Yom HaShoah Interfaith Remembrance
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
