CREATED:20190125T150616Z
DESCRIPTION:Whose Faith is it Anyway? - A Black UU Theological Framework\nB
 lack Lives of UU at UUMontclair and the Undoing Racism Committee invite you
  to join us for a live multi-faith panel discussion. \nJanuary 30th\, 2019 
 - 7:30-10:00pm\nPeierls Room\, UUCM \nThis live discussion will explore the
  ways in which Black Unitarian Universalists and others from related tradit
 ions make sense of our collective faith journeys toward liberation and an a
 ffirmation of wholeness. We will consider: \nWhat are the distinctions betw
 een how Unitarian Universalism is promoted in the larger society vs. our ex
 periences of the faith? \nHow would a Unitarian Universalism grounded in Bl
 ackness be different from what has been taught and promoted about this fait
 h tradition? \nHow do we thoughtfully and responsibly build our own theolog
 y that centers the best of Unitarian Universalism and our experience as Bla
 ck people of faith and consciousness?\nModerated by Rev. Mykal Slack & Dr. 
 Takiyah Amin\nPanelists include: Donte Hilliard an applied social justice p
 ractitioner\, E.N. Hill a third year Masters of Divinity student\, Kimberly
  Hampton\, a consultant with churches and non-profits\, DeReau Farrar\, Dir
 ector of Music\, First Unitarian Portland and Dr. Stephanie Mitchem\, profe
 ssor. \n\nJoin with Google Meet: https://meet.google.com/tov-ggvo-wra\nOr d
 ial: (US) +1 662-547-1284 PIN: 695060307#\n\nLearn more about Meet at: http
 s://support.google.com/a/users/answer/9282720
LAST-MODIFIED:20221206T044714Z
LOCATION:Mortenson
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Whose Faith is it Anyway? - A Black UU Theological Framework
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
