BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20240124T003000Z
DTEND:20240124T014500Z
DTSTAMP:20260311T022957Z
UID:0m5sq71qcdjog82a141bb01fko@google.com
CREATED:20231005T114250Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>This will be a very meaningful group experience at the Unita
 rian Universalist Congregation at Montclair - a six session Covenant Group 
 that invites newcomers and New Members to forge deeper connections with one
  another and with our congregation. </p><p><strong>FAQ</strong></p><ul><li>
 <strong>What if I can’t make every session?</strong> - no worries! If you c
 an make at least 4 sessions that would be great. </li><li><strong>What if I
  need to arrive a tad late?</strong> - no worries. Our sessions will last a
 bout an hour and 15 min. If you can be present for the whole time\, great\,
  but we understand that everyone’s schedule is challenging. </li><li><stron
 g>Do I need to prepare for the sessions?</strong> - no preparation is requi
 red. Some people do like to read the session plan and prepare\, but it is n
 ot necessary. </li><li><strong>What will we do?</strong> - We will begin wi
 th an icebreaker and then follow the plan (the first one is attached) that 
 includes readings\, questions\, and a space for each person to reflect. </l
 i><li><strong>What if I don’t want to share?</strong> - no one is required 
 to share. Passing is totally ok. </li></ul><p>This group will be co-led by 
 Rev. Anya and by two new members and recent New to the U! attendees\, Rache
 l Henry\, and Taylor Henry. </p><p><strong>We will meet at 7:30pm on the 1s
 t and 4th Tuesdays for an hour and a half</strong> including (Tues. 24th Oc
 t.\, Tues. Nov. 7th\, Tues. Nov. 28th\, Tues. Dec. 5th\, Tues. Jan. 2nd (or
  Wed. Jan. 3rd) and Tues. Jan. 23rd) </p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231005T114250Z
LOCATION:Alliance Room\, UUCM
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:New to the U! Fall 2023
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
