DESCRIPTION:Register: <a href="https://tinyurl.com/35pvrmp3">https://tinyur
 l.com/35pvrmp3</a><br>Contact: Jane Gaertner<br><b><br></b><br><span>We inv
 ite you to join members of the Undoing Racism Team on Sunday\, February 9th
  at 1:30 pm at Montclair Art Museum for a free screening of a new  document
 ary: Stronger Than Steel: The Senator Wynona Lipman Story.”</span><br><p di
 r="ltr">We will meet at 1:30 PM in Leir Hall to hear a few comments from Be
 cky Doggett.  Becky is in a brief clip of the documentary.  Leir Hall is th
 e large hall to your right as you enter museum side entrance from parking l
 ot.  Documentary starts at 2 PM.</p><p dir="ltr">Senator Lipman was the fir
 st female African-American woman in the New Jersey State Senate.  She began
  her political career in Montclair and Essex County.  AND Senator Lipman wa
 s also a member and a religious education teacher at UUCM in the early 1970
 s.</p><p dir="ltr">This is a <a href="https://celestebateman.com/about/thew
 ynonalipmanproject/" target="_blank"><u>link to the nonprofit </u></a>which
  produced the documentary\, Blue Butterfly Arts &amp\; Media*\, they ask fo
 r your support. </p><p dir="ltr">Here is the <a href="https://www.montclair
 artmuseum.org/" target="_blank"><u>Museum’s website\,</u></a> if you wish t
 o seek more information.</p><p dir="ltr">So we may know who is coming from 
 UUCM and send you any last minute details\, please rsvp for this event by n
 oon\, Fri.\, Feb. 7th.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250127T150522Z
LOCATION:Montclair Art Museum\, 3 S Mountain Ave\, Montclair\, NJ 07042\, U
 SA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Invitation to Film Screening from URT
TRANSP:OPAQUE
