 : UUCM <br>One tap mobile+13052241968\,\,84269599385#\,\,\,\,*749260# US+13
 092053325\,\,84269599385#\,\,\,\,*749260# US<br><br><br><br>Here is a draft
  agenda and explanation<br><p dir="ltr">Agenda -</p><p dir="ltr">Opening - 
 RS &amp\; JH</p><p dir="ltr">Rounds - who is in the room -  </p><p dir="ltr
 ">        share: name\, roles and aspirations -</p><p dir="ltr"><i>how long
  you have been involved in ministries to children or families? How long as 
 a leader there or elsewhere at UUCM?</i></p><p dir="ltr">Framing - RS\, et 
 al</p><p dir="ltr">Listening - Volunteers take turns sharing what would be 
 beneficial</p><p dir="ltr">Capturing the sharing</p><p dir="ltr">Perspectiv
 e - managing expectations. remembering our capacity and boundaries.</p><p d
 ir="ltr">Action Items</p><p dir="ltr">Closing</p><p dir="ltr">Exeunt</p><br
 >Rationale: Tonight we examine those community building initiatives/program
 s that could help families in the Children's RE program deepen their bonds 
 outside of the Program. <br>These Cohort Programs in no way belong solely t
 o RE. <p dir="ltr">An initiative like this lies at the core of how to stitc
 h the whole community together more effectively over time.</p><p>Note: We a
 re not mtg to discuss the Children’s Religious education program <i>per se<
 /i> - we are working hard on proposals that you will all see soon.</p>
