CREATED:20181204T140607Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>We all experience losses throughout our lifetime\, whether t
 hey are a loss of loved ones\, others important to us\, or important parts 
 of our lives. Grieving our losses can be a lonely experience. People often 
 do not know what to say to a grieving person\; so they may say nothing whic
 h increases a sense of aloneness\; or may behave awkwardly increasing your 
 sense of distance.</p><p>It is hoped that the Grief Support Group will prov
 ide some comfort to those experiencing loss and combat the resulting sense 
 of loneliness in some way. The group provides a caring and confidential env
 ironment that allows its members to share their experiences with others aro
 und their loss. The group is facilitated by an experienced group leader and
  participation guidelines are  provided. This is a support group\, not a th
 erapy group.</p><p><a href="mailto:griefsupport@uumontclair.org" target="_b
 lank">For more information. </a></p><p><br></p><p>Zoom: <a href="https://us
 06web.zoom.us/j/82009940997?pwd=ckMrdjdxYmF5MWZPbk9CZktHbGgxZz09">https://u
 s06web.zoom.us/j/82009940997?pwd=ckMrdjdxYmF5MWZPbk9CZktHbGgxZz09</a></p><p
 >Passcode: UUCM</p>
