DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260311T083000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260311T113000
DTSTAMP:20260311T022957Z
UID:m06pn03mgr1q3r5b80ll1l5ebt_R20251008T130000@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20260311T090000
CREATED:20190716T211908Z
DESCRIPTION:Dear MICA Colleagues\,<br><br>Our next MICA meeting (<b>Wednesd
 ay\, March 11 at Shomrei Emunah</b>) will be a special one. We are planning
  an <b>extended session from 8:30am-11:30am</b> to create unhurried space f
 or reflection on where MICA has been in recent years\, and how we want to s
 hape its future together. <br><br>At our last (Feb 11) meeting\, we began b
 y asking two questions: What do we love and appreciate about MICA? And what
  would we hope to accomplish through a deeper conversation about our missio
 n and how we function as a group? <br><br>A brief summary of what we heard 
 is below. For those who were not present -- or who have additional thoughts
  -- we invite you to contribute through this <a href="https://qualtricsxm2m
 tqrt5v7.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_3t8Vn7pQ7Fugly6" target="_blank">anonymou
 s survey</a>. We'll begin our March 11 meeting by sharing what we've heard.
 <br><br>Our time together will include:<br><ul><li>Personal reflection on t
 he meaning and value MICA holds for each of us\, and how we've been experie
 ncing this forum in recent years</li><li>Group dialogue about where our exp
 eriences align with our shared values -- and where they may not</li><li>Int
 roduction of the idea of MICA as a "community of communities"</li><li>Consu
 ltation on how we can better embody the spirit and purpose that first drew 
 us together and calls us today</li><li>Agreement on concrete next steps</li
 ></ul><br>MICA has long been a rare and meaningful space in our town. We lo
 ok forward to dedicating this time to strengthening it -- with candor\, lov
 e\, and a renewed commitment from all of us. <br><br>With appreciation\,<di
 v dir="auto">Your colleagues <br><br>------------<br><br><b>Notes from our 
 February 11 meeting</b><br><br><i>What we love and appreciate about MICA<br
 ></i><ul><li>Learning from others</li><li>Community</li><li>Diversity</li><
 li>Fellowship</li><li>Connected to the world</li><li>Commitment to justice<
 /li><li>Commitment to one another</li><li>Voice of change in our community<
 /li></ul><i>What we hope to accomplish through a deeper discussion</i><br><
 ul><li>Come together around some specific work we can take on collectively 
 - “forging unity in the fire of solidarity"</li><li>More clarity and intent
 ionality about the role of politics in MICA</li><li>Foster a space for lear
 ning from one another </li></ul>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260310T150132Z
SEQUENCE:4
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Montclair Clergy Associates
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
