DESCRIPTION:Mesh Community Partners Meeting<br><br>Parking at the Unitarian
  Universalist Congregation at Montclair is either on the street or in a nea
 rby garage (Crescent Deck\, North Fullerton Lot\, or Valley &amp\; Bloom De
 ck.) <br><br>Enter through Door C\, which is the Office entrance\, and walk
  up the steps to the second floor (or follow signs to the lift). We will me
 et in the Peierls Room\, which is your first right on the second floor. <br
 ><br>Bagels with fixings will be provided\, as well as coffee and tea. Plea
 se feel welcome to bring your own lunch or supplement\, as dictated by your
  own food restrictions.<br><br>If you are unable to attend\, you are welcom
 e to send another MESH leader in your place. <br><br><br>Goals for our conv
 ersation: <br><ol><li>Better understand MESH&#39\;s financial situation and
  needs. </li><li>Better understand MESH&#39\;s challenges with the town&#39
 \;s leadership. </li><li>Be better prepared to support and advocate for MES
 H&#39\;s ministry. </li><li>Be a part of the ongoing conversations especial
 ly with regard to the role of MESH in supporting a community that is growin
 g in need.</li></ol><br><br>In Faith\, <br>Rev. Anya
LAST-MODIFIED:20260224T154005Z
LOCATION:The Unitarian Universalist Congregation at Montclair\, 67 Church S
 t\, Montclair\, NJ 07042\, USA\, UUCM-1-Peierls (60) [Multiplatform]
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:MESH Community Partners Meeting
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
